main event: A civilian observed a star-like object on the dark rim of the moon for about 5 minutes in Roswell, New Mexico on March 21, 1961.
interesting points: The object appeared stationary and was the size of a bright star.
The object was a white light and was observed on the dark portion of the sky.
The observer was a civilian, a 35-year-old section foreman with Trans-Western Pipeline, with above-average reliability.
The weather was clear with excellent visibility, and wind data was provided for various altitudes.
The report was deemed worthy of forwarding, even though the object was likely just a star, due to its position on the perimeter of the moon.
